==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Redwood
<hw>Red"wood`</hw> <pr>(-w⟦oocr⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A gigantic coniferous tree
(<spn>Sequoia sempervirens</spn>) of California, and its light and
durable reddish timber. See <er>Sequoia</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An
East Indian dyewood, obtained from <spn>Pterocarpus santalinus</spn>,
<spn>Caesalpinia Sappan</spn>, and several other trees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The redwood of Andaman is <spn>Pterocarpus
dalbergioides</spn>; that of some parts of tropical America, several
species of <spn>Erythoxylum</spn>; that of Brazil, the species of
<spn>Humirium</spn>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ree</ent>⟦br⟧
